The African National Congress says it hopes the newly appointed Chief Justice Raymond Zondo will continue to champion the transformation of the judiciary. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced Zondo’s appointment earlier this afternoon. Zondo replaces retired Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. Ramaphosa has also indicated his intention that once the new Chief Justice assumes office, he will nominate Justice Mandisa Maya for the position of Deputy Chief Justice. ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe says they wish Zondo well in his new role. PRESIDENT RAMAPHOSA APPOINTS JUSTICE ZONDO AS CHIEF JUSTICE President @CyrilRamaphosa has in accordance with Section 174(3) of the Constitution, decided to appoint Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo as the next Chief Justice of South Africa with effect from 1 April 2022. pic.twitter.com/6OcDFL7hbT — Presidency | South Africa  (@PresidencyZA) March 10, 2022  The Freedom Front Plus has added its voice to those who have welcomed the appointment of Justice Raymond Zondo as the county’s new Chief Justice. The party says among the candidates interviewed by the JSC, Zondo was their preferred choice. The other candidates were Constitutional Court Justice Mbuyiseli Madlanga, Supreme Court of Appeal President Mandisa Maya and Gauteng Judge President Dunstan Mlambo. Raymond Zondo appointed as Chief Justice “President Cyril Ramaphosa has chosen a safe pair of hands in appointing Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo as the next Chief Justice. Judge Zondo has a clear track record and will go a long way in restoring faith in the judiciary.” – @jsteenhuisen, DA Leader  pic.twitter.com/iGOdcYs5ss — Democratic Alliance (@Our_DA) March 10, 2022 